description:
Bug 3666 - Code Completion - Hungry code assist (1GDRYW5)
jkca (5/15/2001 11:04:56 AM)
jresdk 106

Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature eats too much code. Consider the enclosed class. As a programmer, I must add a parameter to the baz call in bar to make the program correct.

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Open the provided class X.
2. In the bar method, add a parameter to the baz call.

OB: The code is changed to:

baz(x.foo().foo())

I would rather it gave me baz(x.foo()x.foo())

public class X {
	void bar(X x) {
		baz(x.foo());
	}

	int foo() {
		return 5;
	}

	void baz(int i, int j) {

	}
}

